<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Explain the Code 📖</h2>
<p>Here is a working inventory. The hero starts with a <strong>list</strong> of items, and the code shows them on screen.</p>
<pre><code class="language-python">inventory = [&quot;map&quot;, &quot;key&quot;, &quot;torch&quot;]
game.say(f&quot;You carry: {inventory[0]}, {inventory[1]}, {inventory[2]}&quot;)
game.say(f&quot;The first item in your inventory is the {inventory[0]}.&quot;)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What is the name of the list, and what three values are inside it?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong><code>inventory[0]</code> gives which item? Why that one and not the second?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Which index would you use to show the <code>torch</code>?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>The last line says "the first item." What does the word <em>index</em> mean in your own words?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

